{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3154868,"name":"fovea1959","username":"fovea1959","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/fovea1959/{size}/5301_2.png","created_at":"2023-02-28T23:34:25.247Z","cooked":"<p>In years past, a program could tell if the roboRIO clock was set by looking at the date/time; the roboRIO would boot up with the date back at the epoch (1970).</p>
<p>This year, it appears that is no longer the case; one of our roboRIOs comes up with a date earlier this month. It appears that the roboRIO is using /etc/timestamp to set the system start time now.</p>
<p>Is there a reliable way to tell if the date/time in the RIO has been set from the DS?</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2023-02-28T23:34:25.247Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":80,"reads":212,"readers_count":211,"score":442.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":428487,"topic_slug":"how-to-tell-when-date-time-are-correct-on-roborio","display_username":"fovea1959","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":15648,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Herder of 3620 Programmers / LRI / CSA"},"post_url":"/t/how-to-tell-when-date-time-are-correct-on-roborio/428487/1","custom_user_title":"Herder of 3620 Programmers / LRI / CSA","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3155075,"name":"Peter Johnson","username":"Peter_Johnson","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/peter_johnson/{size}/10417_2.png","created_at":"2023-03-01T04:07:27.387Z","cooked":"<p>It should be getting set with the first few packets of DS UDP data.  What we do in DataLogManager is wait for the DS to be attached for ~1 second.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2023-03-01T04:07:51.446Z","reply_count":4,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":186,"readers_count":185,"score":77.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":