<p>do I need to worry about .isFMSAttached(), or is the DS the only place we get date/time from?</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2023-03-02T04:06:24.289Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":157,"readers_count":156,"score":36.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":428487,"topic_slug":"how-to-tell-when-date-time-are-correct-on-roborio","display_username":"fovea1959","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":13575,"username":"Peter_Johnson","name":"Peter Johnson","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/peter_johnson/{size}/10417_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":15648,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Herder of 3620 Programmers / LRI / CSA"},"post_url":"/t/how-to-tell-when-date-time-are-correct-on-roborio/428487/3","custom_user_title":"Herder of 3620 Programmers / LRI / CSA","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3155741,"name":"marshall","username":"marshall","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/marshall/{size}/167657_2.png","created_at":"2023-03-02T04:20:44.874Z","cooked":"<p>It’s not something most teams need but a way to override this and just use NTP from the other systems would be really nice.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2023-03-02T04:20:44.874Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":5,"reads":147,"readers_count":146,"score":69.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":428487,"topic_slug":"how-to-tell-when-date-time-are-correct-on-roborio","display_username":"marshall","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":13575,"username":"Peter_Johnson","name":"Peter Johnson","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/peter_johnson/{size}/10417_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":17672,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Team Principal"},"post_url":"/t/how-to-tell-when-date-time-are-correct-on-roborio/428487/4","custom_user_title":"Team Principal","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3156567,"name":"fovea1959","username":"fovea1959","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/fovea1959/{size}/5301_2.png","created_at":"2023-03-03T15:58:29.091Z","cooked":"<p>I tried to replicate what DataLogManager does, but consecutive isDSAttached() for 100 iterations in a loop with a 20ms sleep is not enough time to reliably have an update date/time. The only thing I can think of is that the Thread.sleep() is getting interrupted. Will come back to it Saturday, gotta inspect robots tomorrow.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">    private static void watchForDS() {
        Date start = new Date();
        int consecutives = 0;
        while (!Thread.interrupted()) {
            if (DriverStation.isDSAttached()) {
                if (consecutives++ &gt;= 100) { // 100 times at 20 ms is two second
                    _timestamp = new Date();
                    StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder("timestamp for logs set: ");
                    sb.append(convertTimestampToString(_timestamp));
                    sb.append(", was ");
                    sb.append(convertTimestampToString(start));
                    System.out.println(sb.toString());
                    break;
                }
            } else {
                consecutives = 0;
            }
            try {
                Thread.sleep(20); // wait 20ms
            } catch (InterruptedException ex) {
                // nothing
            }
        }
    }

</code></pre>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2023-03-03T15:58:29.091Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":80,"readers_count":79,"score":21.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":428487,"topic_slug":"how-to-tell-when-date-time-are-correct-on-roborio","display_username":"fovea1959","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":13575,"username":"Peter_Johnson","name":"Peter Johnson","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/peter_johnson/{size}/10417_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":15648,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Herder of 3620 Programmers / LRI / CSA"},"post_url":"/t/how-to-tell-when-date-time-are-correct-on-roborio/428487/5","custom_user_title":"Herder of 3620 Programmers / LRI / CSA","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3156573,"name":"Peter Johnson","username":"Peter_Johnson","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/peter_johnson/{size}/10417_2.png","created_at":"2023-03-03T16:26:03.594Z","cooked":"<p>It may be that DataLogManager doesn’t end up with a reliable time either with the change to the image.  But I’ll need to dig further to understand the timeline of the clock set in NetComm.</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2023-03-03T16:26:03.594Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_co